## Stirling PDF (upstream base)

This project bundles or integrates [**Stirling PDF**](https://github.com/Stirling-Tools/Stirling-PDF)
via the `stirling-upstream/` submodule and portable desktop builds. Stirling PDF
uses a **mixed license**: most of the codebase is MIT, while some directories
(`engine/`, `app/proprietary/`, parts of `frontend/`, etc.) have separate terms.

See:

- [licenses/STIRLING-PDF-LICENSE](licenses/STIRLING-PDF-LICENSE) — upstream LICENSE text (verbatim)
- [THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md](THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md) — distribution summary
- [docs/plan/07-license-compliance.md](docs/plan/07-license-compliance.md) — compliance notes

French Reading Assistant is a **third-party extension**, not an official Stirling PDF product.
